metadata.name: Raymarching explorer #2
metadata.description:
Concept.
Finally, you have been reduced to a particle, you can travel through the light to see as little as possible.Just keep the steering wheel, I'm sure you'll go somewhere.


Technical Information.
Raymarching explorer is an interactive piece where you can travel through a procedural raymarching world. GLSL shader mixed with P5js (thanks to kali for helping me solving the camera movement).


Interaction.
- Click and hold left button to control the light with the mouse position.
- Use W A S D E Q keys for moving the camera arround like a FPS.

metadata.name: FXHASH Generative Logo #378
metadata.description:
Unique iteration of the first Generative Token minted on fxhash.

It also servers as the actual logo of the platform. It represents the generative processes driving fxhash tokens. Generative Tokens are fed with a unique hash to produce unique outputs based on the hash ‚Äî they are functions with a hash as single input.

The growth that comes out of the text is driven by a "Dividing-Aggregating Walkers" (DAW) algorithm. The hash drives all the DAW settings, as well as a mutation factor which is responsible for changes in each Walker parameters as they divide.

Some iterations will produce very simple outputs whereas others might be more chaotic.

Piece by @ciphrd for fxhash

metadata.name: Digital Surface 1 #5
metadata.description:
The mechanics of Digital Surface is inspired by nature and the aesthetics by pixels. Digital Surface is an attempt to find an autonomous visual logic for a digital world made by machines.
The image is created one pixel after another, calculating the proceeding pixel based on the previous generations.
The color palettes are influenced by colors occurring in nature mixed with artificial man made colors that we see more today, aiming to look for new combinations that are pleasant to humans and natively digital.

Render time can be long. Once the image is completed, press "s" to save in a small size, "m" in a medium, "l" in a large, "x" in a xlarge and "w" to save with the size of the window.

Digital Surface is a 5 series project. Each Series is released singularly, the first being Digital Surface 1. The main differentiation for series 1 is that each image contains 2 colors.
This is Francesco Forcellini Studio's first NFT project broadening their field of work from physical to digital.

Built using p5js, published under CC-BY-NC-4.0 license.

Once the collection will be fully minted, the variations button will be disabled.

metadata.name: Cradle #106
metadata.description:
Billions of years old, ancient remains decay across our Solar System. Mere transient visitors to our star, their ephemeral presence on our worlds is embodied in their creations. In the shadow of their megalithic constructions, we wonder what they might have brought to us.

They brought life.

----

Live mode controls:
'r' - change resolution
's' - save PNG
'f' - render at full speed
'space' - stop/continue rendering

The image quality gradually improves over time. The rendering speed is reduced by default - press 'f' for the maximum speed.

Rendering may be GPU intensive.

metadata.name: Interdependency #7
metadata.description:
"Interdependency" is the third collection released as a part of NeoMent's "Abandoned Reality" series.

Established systems are fragile. All elements of the system depend on each other, and at the same time allow all others to exist. What happens if one element disappears? The beautiful, harmonic, established system completely refuses to function, it shatters into tiny pieces. It's unrecoverable. It's gone. Probably forever.

metadata.name: Ignorance is Bliss #3
metadata.description:
"Ignorance is Bliss" is the second collection released as a part of NeoMent's "Abandoned Reality" series.

People often argue over things that are not under their control. But why bother? At the end of the day, your opinion won't change anything unless you have the power to accomplish that change. Of course you can say that you are aguing for "The Truth" or "Justice", but what's the point in your bickering if you aren't going to accomplish anything?
But you can go even further than that, you can choose to ignore global problems completely, live in your own world. One who doesn't know of a problem shan't worry about it - thus, ignorance is bliss. 
Is it right or is it wrong? What's the point in arguing over what I wrote if you won't change anything? All you can do is decide for yourself.

metadata.name: Pobbles #65
metadata.description:
The pobbles are generative blob-rocks: staring in silence, sometimes half-smiling, generally bored. 

‚Ä¢ The pobbles are digital recreations of a series of rock-doodles by S.F.Kislev (my big brother). They are an attempt to capture a specific, singular handwriting, and evolve it using code. 
‚Ä¢ See the original, 2014 handmade version here - https://pobbles.tez.page..
‚Ä¢ Alternative titles considered include Peggles‚Ñ¢, Plops‚Ñ¢, Blobbies‚Ñ¢, Floofs‚Ñ¢, Flintstones‚Ñ¢, Lardies‚Ñ¢, Plumps‚Ñ¢, Fats‚Ñ¢ and Wet-Ones‚Ñ¢. 
‚Ä¢ The pobbles are written entirely in paper.js and p5.js. 
‚Ä¢ The pobbles are an effort to take generative art into the realm of the cute. 
‚Ä¢ They work well with toddlers.

metadata.name: Pages From A Redacted Document #45
metadata.description:
In a time of mistrust, fear and corruption this work looks to reflect how transparency and accountability are removed from those with responsibility with a simple black line.

An abstract representation of the murky world that lurks behind the corridors of power. Kept there hidden and away from the masses.  We demand more.

A representation of documents printed and hand written, that are augmented with highlighters and blocking out pens.

press 'S' to download the hi-res version, which will show the full detail.
